#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:1
msgid "System-specific package options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:3
msgid "The following outlines system-specific configuration options available for packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:7
msgid "`LIBFOO_VSDEVCMD`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:10
#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:40
msgid "The option is ignored in non-Windows environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:16
msgid "Allows a package to automatically load Visual Studio Developer Command Prompt (`VsDevCmd.bat`) variables into the releng-tool process. This will allow a package to invoke commands as if releng-tool was started from within a Visual Studio Developer Command Prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:25
msgid "A package looking to use an explicit version of Visual Studio can specify a version string that is compatible with [Visual Studio Locator's][vswhere] (vswhere) `-version` argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:33
msgid "See also [`vsdevcmd`](conf-vsdevcmd) and [`LIBFOO_VSDEVCMD_PRODUCTS`](pkg-opt-vsdevcmd-products)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:37
msgid "`LIBFOO_VSDEVCMD_PRODUCTS`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:46
msgid "Allows a package to configure which products to search for when releng-tool invokes [Visual Studio Locator][vswhere] to find which Visual Studio tooling to use. By default, releng-tool operates as if `vswhere` is invoked with the `-products *` argument. Providing a string in this option replaces the asterisk value with the configured value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/system-pkg-options.md:56
msgid "See also [`vsdevcmd_products`](conf-vsdevcmd-products) and [`LIBFOO_VSDEVCMD`](pkg-opt-vsdevcmd)."
msgstr ""
